&gt; (politics, tv, religion, car salesmen, diets, advertisements, etc).
&gt;
&gt; So to answer your question &quot;Also, I don&#39;t get why anyone who is a skeptic
&gt; would belong to this group?&quot;.  Doubting and questioning results can only
&gt; make a field of research more  solid in the long run.  It helps to divide
&gt; the weak evidence and methods from the strong.   While everyone is still
&gt; free to pursue their beliefs, everyone only has so much time and money,  and
&gt; getting help with determining the best areas to spend that time and money
&gt; can be a valuable thing.
&gt;
&gt; So for anyone doing research, especially their own personal research, who
&gt; is not wealthy and does not have 100 years left in their lives, being
&gt; skeptical about one&#39;s results seems not only a necessity, but I don&#39;t think
&gt; any kind of progress, especially in a difficult area like the paranormal, is
&gt; even possible without it.
